## Response Helpers (Centralized)

Create a shared module of response helper functions. Every API handler uses these instead of manually constructing responses:

```
// lib/responseHelpers.ts (or equivalent)
ok(data)           -> 200 + JSON body
created(data)      -> 201 + JSON body
badRequest(msg)    -> 400 + { error: msg }
unauthorized()     -> 401 + { error: "Unauthorized" }
forbidden(msg)     -> 403 + { error: msg }
notFound(msg)      -> 404 + { error: msg }
conflict(msg)      -> 409 + { error: msg }
unprocessable(msg) -> 422 + { error: msg }
parseBody(request) -> parsed JSON body (returns 400 if invalid)
isValidId(id)      -> boolean (validates DB ID format)
```

**Why:** Consistent response format everywhere, no typos in status codes, easy to change structure globally.

---

## Database Error Mapper

Create a shared function that maps known database errors to proper HTTP responses:

```
// lib/databaseErrors.ts (or equivalent)
function handleDatabaseError(error):
  -> Duplicate key (e.g. unique constraint violation)  -> 409 conflict("A record with this value already exists.")
  -> Validation error             -> 400 badRequest(errorDetailsFrom(error))
  -> Cast error / invalid ID      -> 400 badRequest("Invalid ID format.")
  -> Unknown                      -> 500 + log the error (never expose raw error to client)
```

**Why:** Prevents inconsistent 500s for known error types. Every handler's catch block should call the shared mapper instead of writing custom error mapping per handler.

