## Field Allowlists (API Projections)

Never return full DB records to the client. Define a **field allowlist** per entity for API responses:

```
// lib/fieldAllowlists.ts (or equivalent - one per entity)
const USER_PUBLIC_FIELDS = ["id", "name", "email", "image", "role"];
const USER_ADMIN_FIELDS  = [...USER_PUBLIC_FIELDS, "createdAt", "lastLogin", "status"];

function getFieldsForRole(entity, role) -> returns the appropriate field list
```

- Maintain one source of truth for which fields each role can see
- Use DB projections/select to fetch only needed fields (don't fetch all then filter)
- NEVER accidentally return `password`, `hashedToken`, `internalNotes`, or other sensitive fields
- When entities grow, update the allowlist - not every handler individually

